|CKBStreet Samurai Cortex Network|000

|CK0The Cortex network is restricted to authenticated Street Samurai members.
Its messages, emotes, media shares, history, login notices, and logout notices
are not sent to nonmembers or external channel bridges. An inactive contract
still retains membership and network access.|000

|CKBTransmitting|000
|CK0samchat <message> sends a normal transmission.
samchat :<emote> uses channel-emote syntax.
esamchat <message> uses narrative egossip-style syntax.
The channel supports the same speech, emote, and shared-media forms as gossip.
Sending while reception is muted restores the channel automatically.|000

|CKBDisplay color|000
|CK0Use color street_samurai to select the foreground, background, and effect
used for Cortex network traffic. This preference applies when sending, receiving,
or reviewing newly recorded transmissions through samhist.|000

|CKBHistory and operators|000
|CK0samhist shows recent Cortex transmissions; supply a line count when you
need more or less than the normal view. samwho runs a shell-style listing of
visible connected members. Invisible operators remain hidden when the viewer
would not normally be able to see them.|000

|CKBsamwho fields|000
|CK0samwho reports name, Guild Level, Cortex Rank, Edge, Heat, strain, contract
state, and current activity. PRIMARY and SECONDARY are active membership states.
INACTIVE means guild systems are paused by an equipment conflict. SIGNAL LOST,
IDLE, IN COMBAT, and COMMS MUTED describe connection or activity rather than
hardware condition.|000

|CKBTroubleshooting|000
|CK0If you can read but not transmit, check silence effects and normal channel
restrictions. If the channel was muted, sending samchat restores reception.
Samhist confirms whether a message reached the network; samwho confirms which
visible operators are currently connected.|000
